Story: SEEDCO has donated 2500 Sinopharm doses to government for vaccination of Agritex staff against COVID-19.  The seed company has also partnered with Cimas Medical Aid Society to pool resources for the vaccination campaign.  Local Government minister July Moyo, who received the donation together with Lands and Agriculture minister Anxious Masuka at  Seed Cos Stapleford depot in Harare, said the vaccine would go a long way in safeguarding Agritex officers and farmers, who regularly engage in face-to-face interaction.  I am so pleased that more than 98% of the Seed Co employees and their families have been vaccinated. Other companies should follow suit, Moyo said.  Seed Co has also assisted several journalists to get vaccinated.
Ministry of Health published that they had 8,285,000 vaccines in storage to date. We are not sure where the rest of the dosages came from. We subtracted the existing records to match the given figure
